<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3629] Parser sets exitcode on errors, but generator does not</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3629</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;main.cc&lt;/tt&gt;, the &lt;tt&gt;parse()&lt;/tt&gt; function and the &lt;tt&gt;generate()&lt;/tt&gt; function do behave inconsistently w/regard to exceptions being thrown. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both functions catch the exception, but ...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;parse()&lt;/tt&gt; exits with code 1 and prints the error to &lt;tt&gt;stderr&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;generate()&lt;/tt&gt; only prints the error to &lt;tt&gt;stdout&lt;/tt&gt; and finally exits with code 0&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Proposal is to change &lt;tt&gt;generate()&lt;/tt&gt; similar to the behaviour of &lt;tt&gt;parse()&lt;/tt&gt;. Patch is ready, follows.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
